<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Episode 1: Barnyard Burnout</h1>
    <p>The wild first race of Cluck Diesel!</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Opening Scene</h2>
    <p>
      🎵 The theme song kicks in while the title “Chicken Butt Cars” slams across the screen in corn-yellow letters. 
      Cluck Diesel zooms past the screen, leaving feathers and dust.
    </p>

    <h2>The Barnyard Track</h2>
    <p>
      The camera pans over a dusty barn. Tractors are parked, hay bales stacked. 
      Cluck Diesel revs up, feathers shaking, his tail spoiler gleaming. 
      Other chickens watch nervously: “Cluck… are you sure this track is safe?” 
      Cluck Diesel: <em>“Safe? No. Fun? Absolutely.”</em>
    </p>

    <h2>The First Race</h2>
    <p>
      Cluck Diesel lines up against <strong>Grease Beak</strong>, a scrappy rival with oil-stained feathers. 
      A pig waves the checkered flag with its curly tail. 
      “3…2…1…CLUCK!” 🏁 They’re off!
    </p>

    <h2>Chaos in the Cornfield</h2>
    <p>
      They blast out of the barn and into the cornfield. Chickens dodge tractors, jump over irrigation pipes, 
      and get splashed clean by sprinklers. Cluck Diesel pulls a <strong>mirror flip</strong> off a hay bale ramp — 
      the crowd goes wild!
    </p>

    <h2>The Finish</h2>
    <p>
      At the last second, Grease Beak spins out into a haystack. 
      Cluck Diesel skids across the finish line, feathers smoking like burnt tires. 
      The crowd cheers: “CLUCK! CLUCK! CLUCK!”  
      Cluck Diesel, calm and cool: <em>“Fueled by corn, powered by chaos.”</em>
    </p>

    <h2>Closing Scene</h2>
    <p>
      A “Next Time On Chicken Butt Cars” teaser shows new racers arriving in the barnyard. 
      The adventure has just begun.
    </p>

